first_block.description:
At t={current_time}, checking ready queue for shortest burst...

Ready processes: {ready_list}
Shortest burst: {process_id} with burst time {burst}

{process_id} starts execution and will run to completion.

process_complete.description:
Process {process_id} finishes execution!

Burst time: {burst} (shortest available when selected)
Started at t={start_time}, completed at t={end_time}.
Waiting time: {wait_time}
Turnaround time: {tat}

final.description:
SJF Scheduling Complete!

Execution Order: {execution_order}
(Processes ran in order of shortest burst, not arrival!)

Metrics:
{metrics}

Average Waiting Time: {avg_wait}
Average Turnaround Time: {avg_tat}

Note: SJF minimizes average waiting time but can cause starvation for long processes.
